  "body": "I am trying to mount an `<html>` element onto `document`\n\nHere is the code I'm trying to run in the browser (I am using Browserify):\n\n``` javascript\n/** @jsx React.DOM */\n'use strict';\n\nvar React = require('react')\nReact.allowFullPageRender = true\n\nvar App = require('./')\n\ndocument.addEventListener(\"DOMContentLoaded\", function() {\n  React.renderComponent(<App />, document)\n})\n```\n\nand here is a fiddle with the same result:\nhttp://jsfiddle.net/andrezsanchez/wQbD9/\n\nThe `allowFullPageRender` option doesn't seem to be working; I am getting the same error that I was getting when the option was not set:\n\n```\nUncaught Error: Invariant Violation: mountComponentIntoNode(...): Target container is not valid.\n```\n",
